text.section:
An individual who is a classroom teacher or a teacher at a State or local correctional facility or a juvenile facility listed in § 9-226 of the Human Services Article and who holds a standard professional certificate or an advanced professional certificate may claim a credit against the State income tax for up to $1,500 of tuition paid by the individual during the taxable year for graduate level courses required to maintain certification if the individual:
successfully completes the courses with a grade of B or better;
is employed by a county board of educationa State or local correctional facility, or a juvenile facility listed in § 9-226 of the Human Services Article;
teaches in a public schoola State or local correctional facility, or a juvenile facility listed in § 9-226 of the Human Services Article and receives a satisfactory performance evaluation for that teaching; and
has not been reimbursed by the State or a county for the tuition paid.
